        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add reset family carryover summaries",
        "body": "## Behavior or issue addressed\n\nDepends on #90239.\n\nWhen a session has been reset/rotated, the active transcript can be clean while the previous reset archive still contains the latest compaction summary. The next embedded-agent prompt therefore starts without the carryover context unless the model/tool explicitly asks for family history.\n\nThis change reuses the session-family transcript resolver from #90239 and injects the latest reset-archive compaction summary into the embedded-agent prompt context before the LLM boundary, but only when the active context does not already contain a compaction summary.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Move the #90239 family/reset transcript target resolver into a shared gateway helper.\n- Keep `chat.history(includeFamily)` on the shared resolver.\n- Pass the current session store path/entry into embedded-agent attempts.\n- Add a prompt-context transform that prepends one `compactionSummary` from reset ancestor transcripts.\n- Skip injection when the active session already has a compaction summary.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** When the active post-reset session has no compaction summary but a reset ancestor transcript has a persisted compaction row, the embedded-agent prompt context should carry the active reset-ancestor branch summary forward once before the LLM boundary without reading unowned reset archives.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local upstream checkout at `/home/clever/.openclaw/workspace/github/openclaw` on branch `pr-90259`, current head `e2fa523f667e99df74c97917a02c2fc3a8f2c0ee`, using the real TypeScript source modules and temporary on-disk OpenClaw-like session stores/transcripts under `/tmp`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after the patch:**\n\n1. Created an on-disk session store where `main` points at a clean active session and `usageFamilySessionIds` includes an older reset ancestor.\n2. Wrote owned reset-archive JSONL files with valid session headers plus newer colliding/headerless archive files that must not be read.\n3. Invoked the real gateway `chat.history` RPC with `includeFamily: true` and the embedded-agent carryover resolver/transform against those files.\n4. Re-ran prompt snapshot verification after the merge and archive-safety changes.\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\nTerminal capture from current head:\n\n```text\n$ npm run test -- src/gateway/server.chat.gateway-server-chat-b.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-family-carryover.test.ts\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  80 passed (80)\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  5 passed (5)\n\n$ npm run prompt:snapshots:check\nPrompt snapshots are current (7 files).\n\n$ git diff --check\n# no output\n```\n\nThe local targeted run above completed on current head `e2fa523f66` after fixing the `checks-node-agentic-control-plane-agent-chat` regression caused by importing `session-utils` before the gateway test mocks were installed.\n\n**Observed result after fix:**\n\n- Live gateway-history output path: `chat.history(includeFamily)` reads the owned reset ancestor archive and active ancestor transcript, while rejecting a newer colliding `ancestor-session-topic-secret...` archive and a headerless topic archive.\n- Live embedded-agent prompt carryover path: the carryover resolver selects the owned ancestor compaction summary and ignores an unowned newer reset archive before prompt carryover.\n- The prompt-boundary transform prepends carryover exactly once and skips raw model runs.\n- Prompt snapshots remain current after the merge and archive-safety changes.\n\n**Implementation safety proof added in this head:**\n\n- Family history now reuses `resolveSessionTranscriptResetArchiveCandidatesAsync`, the existing bounded/cached/header-checked reset archive resolver, instead of the previous filename-prefix directory scan.\n- The unsafe `isResetArchiveForSession` / unbounded `discoverResetArchiveTranscriptFiles` path was removed.\n- `resolveSessionTranscriptResetArchiveCandidatesAsync` is exported through `session-utils` so gateway family history and embedded-agent carryover share the same reset archive ownership checks.\n\n**What was not tested:** Full end-to-end Telegram reset turn against a live gateway was not run locally. The current-head tests exercise the real gateway history RPC path and the embedded-agent carryover transform/resolver against real on-disk session artifacts.",
        "branch": "fix/session-carryover-summary",
